## Why This Is Asked
Tests practical usage of scheduled exports, storage event triggers, and idempotent processing in a basic backup workflow. It also evaluates IAM scoping and lifecycle management.

## Key Concepts
- Cloud Scheduler for periodic tasks
- Cloud SQL export to Cloud Storage
- Cloud Functions triggered by storage events (objectFinalize)
- Idempotent file naming and conditional processing
- Storage Lifecycle rules for retention

## Code Example
```javascript
// Cloud Function (Node.js) skeleton
const {Storage} = require('@google-cloud/storage');
const storage = new Storage();

exports.backupPostProcess = async (event, context) => {
  const bucketName = event.bucket;
  const srcName = event.name; // e.g., dumps/db-20260113.sql.gz
  const destName = srcName
    .replace('dumps/', 'backups/archived/')
    .replace(/\.gz$/, '.sql.gz');
  const bucket = storage.bucket(bucketName);
  const dest = bucket.file(destName);
  const [exists] = await dest.exists();
  if (exists) return;
  await bucket.file(srcName).copy(dest);
  await bucket.file(srcName).delete();
};
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you verify idempotency across multiple runs?
- How would you handle a failed export and implement retries with alerting?

